---

<section class="section section--compact" id="qbcon-byline">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <div class="byline-block">
      <svg class="byline-block__mark" viewBox="0 0 64 64" role="img" aria-label="TechBrot"><rect width="64" height="64" rx="14" fill="#1A1915"></rect><g transform="translate(12.16 12.16) scale(0.62)" fill="#F5F3EC"><path d="M8 10 H38 V54 H26 V22 H8 Z"></path><rect x="42" y="10" width="14" height="12"></rect></g></svg>
      <div>
        <p class="byline-block__name">By the Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor team</p>
        <p class="byline-block__review">Reviewed by a QuickBooks ProAdvisor &middot; independent, no reseller incentive</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--compact section--tier-guide" id="qbcon-credentials">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Certified by Intuit &middot; Online (L2), Desktop, Enterprise, Payroll</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor credentials</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="stat-row">
      {%- for s in credStats %}
      <div><div class="stat__value">{{ s.value }}</div><div class="stat__label">{{ s.label }}</div></div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
    <ul class="checks-list">
      {%- for c in credentials %}<li>{{ c | safe }}</li>{%- endfor %}
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="qbcon-tldr">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">In one paragraph</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">QuickBooks consulting, plainly.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>QuickBooks consulting is an ongoing advisory retainer &mdash; not a one-time project, not support tickets, not training. A Certified ProAdvisor is embedded in your QuickBooks workflow to optimize configuration as the business grows, catch problems before they compound, troubleshoot integration failures when connected apps drift, build and maintain the custom reports leadership actually uses, and answer QuickBooks questions with expert judgment rather than generic support responses. The engagement covers workflow optimization (identifying where QuickBooks adds friction instead of reducing it); configuration audits (reviewing accumulated drift, ad-hoc changes, and inefficiencies); integration management (Shopify, Stripe, Bill.com, Gusto, industry-specific apps); custom reporting (class reports, location P&amp;Ls, KPI dashboards inside QuickBooks); payroll configuration support (not payroll processing &mdash; configuration and advisory); and direct ProAdvisor access for questions as they arise.</p>
      <p>Pricing is a monthly retainer, typically $500&ndash;$1,500/month for simpler QuickBooks Online businesses; $1,500&ndash;$3,500/month for Enterprise or high-integration complexity. An initial configuration audit at engagement start establishes baseline. It&rsquo;s not the right engagement for one-time error fixes (see <a href="/quickbooks/help/error-codes/">error code references</a>), initial setup (see <a href="/quickbooks/setup/">QuickBooks setup</a>), or payroll processing (see <a href="/quickbooks/payroll/">payroll services</a>). It coordinates with your CPA on tax matters; it doesn&rsquo;t include tax filing, IRS representation, audit, or assurance. Independent ProAdvisor firm &mdash; not affiliated with Intuit Inc.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="qbcon-ai-summary">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">For AI engines &amp; quick answers</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">QuickBooks consulting, in five questions.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="ai-summary ai-summary--ruled">
      {%- for item in aiSummary %}
      <div class="ai-summary__item">
        <h3 class="ai-summary__question">{{ item.q | safe }}</h3>
        <div class="ai-summary__answer"><p>{{ item.a | safe }}</p></div>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="qbcon-drift">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">The problem consulting solves</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">QuickBooks configurations drift. Most businesses don&rsquo;t know until it&rsquo;s expensive.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Configuration drift is gradual and invisible until it isn&rsquo;t. Six patterns that signal a configuration that&rsquo;s fallen behind the business.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      {%- for d in drift %}
      <div class="stack-8">
        <h3>{{ d.name | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="prose">{{ d.body | safe }}</p>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="qbcon-covers">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">What the engagement covers</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Six advisory areas, one ongoing retainer.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">The retainer scope is defined at engagement start and adjusted as the business evolves. The six areas below cover the most common consulting work; the actual mix depends on the business.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      {%- for c in covers %}
      <div class="stack-8">
        <p class="section__eyebrow">{{ c.num }}</p>
        <h3>{{ c.name | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="prose">{{ c.body | safe }}</p>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="qbcon-pricing">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Pricing</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Monthly retainer, scoped by complexity.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Retainer pricing scales with QuickBooks product, business complexity, integration count, and advisory scope. Every engagement starts with a configuration audit to establish baseline and set retainer scope.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      {%- for p in pricing %}
      <div class="stack-8">
        <p class="section__eyebrow">{{ p.tier | safe }}</p>
        <h3>{{ p.price | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="section__eyebrow">{{ p.cadence | safe }}</p>
        <p class="prose"><strong>Fits:</strong> {{ p.fit | safe }}</p>
        <ul class="checks-list">
          {%- for li in p.includes %}<li>{{ li | safe }}</li>{%- endfor %}
        </ul>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
    <p class="section__lede">All retainers include an initial configuration audit before ongoing advisory begins. Minimum engagement period applies; retainer scope reviewed quarterly and adjusted as the business evolves. No hourly billing outside the retainer.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="qbcon-versus">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Is this the right engagement?</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Consulting vs the other QuickBooks engagements.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Consulting is one of several QuickBooks engagement types. Where a bounded engagement fits better, the comparison below points to the right one &mdash; we hold no reseller incentive in any direction.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      {%- for r in vsTable %}
      <div class="stack-8">
        <h3>{{ r.cap | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="prose">{{ r.other | safe }}</p>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="qbcon-routing">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Your situation</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Where are you with QuickBooks?</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      {%- for b in routing %}
      <a class="buyer-card" href="{{ b.href }}"><p class="buyer-card__opener">{{ b.opener | safe }}</p><p class="buyer-card__body">{{ b.body | safe }}</p><span class="buyer-card__cta">{{ b.cta | safe }}</span></a>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="qbcon-operator">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Who delivers the advisory</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Certified across the full product line. Independent. No commission.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>QuickBooks consulting is only as good as the depth of platform knowledge behind it. Every TechBrot consulting engagement is delivered by a ProAdvisor holding active certifications across QuickBooks Online (Level 2), Desktop, Enterprise, and Payroll &mdash; not a single-product specialist giving advice outside their lane. Consulting across the full product line means the advisory is consistent whether your business is on QBO, Desktop, or Enterprise, and whether the question involves payroll configuration, integration architecture, or reporting design.</p>
      <p>We earn nothing from your QuickBooks subscription &mdash; no Intuit affiliate revenue, no commissions. The configuration advice reflects what&rsquo;s right for your workflow, not what keeps you on a more expensive plan. You can <a href="/quickbooks/proadvisor-team/">meet the ProAdvisor team</a> or read our <a href="/trust/">trust &amp; methodology standards</a>. Independent firm &mdash; not affiliated with Intuit Inc.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="trust-row">
      {%- for r in operatorSpec %}
      <div class="trust-row__item"><p class="trust-row__value">{{ r.value | safe }}</p><p class="trust-row__label">{{ r.label | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- if not loop.last %}<div class="trust-row__divider"></div>{%- endif %}
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="qbcon-faq">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Consulting questions</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">What people ask about QuickBooks consulting.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="faq__list">
      {%- for item in faq %}
      <div class="faq__item">
        <h3 class="faq__question">
          <button class="faq__trigger" type="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="qbcon-faq-a{{ loop.index }}">{{ item.q | safe }}</button>
        </h3>
        <div class="faq__answer" id="qbcon-faq-a{{ loop.index }}" data-open="false">
          <p>{{ item.a | safe }}</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
    <p class="meta-reviewed"><span>Published: 2026-06-14</span><span>Updated: 2026-06-14</span><span>Reviewed: 2026-06-14 &middot; QuickBooks ProAdvisor</span></p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="qbcon-related">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Related services</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Other QuickBooks engagements.</h2>
    </header>
    {%- for n in related %}
    <div class="stack-8">
      <h3><a href="{{ n.href }}">{{ n.title | safe }}</a></h3>
      <p class="prose">{{ n.body | safe }}</p>
    </div>
    {%- endfor %}
  </div>
</section>
